@sven-lange-last @mhenke1 
Thank you for the feedback :)

Following yours feedback, I will create a test toggle.

@markusthoemmes @rabbah I think I addressed your review comments. Please check and let me know.

@rabbah concerning your comment / request:

> I think this is a dilation factor we can move to the configuration parameters.

I didn't fully expose this factor as a configuration parameter yet because we were fine so far with also having other timeouts as `val`s local to the class. See https://github.com/apache/openwhisk/blob/b5b88ece0ae08c87948796b38ab18e55ab4b70a7/core/invoker/src/main/scala/org/apache/openwhisk/core/containerpool/docker/DockerContainer.scala#L176-L178

* That's why I renamed one of the timeouts for more clarity and added `logCollectingTimeoutPerMBLogLimit` to this list.
* I suggest that we should expose all or none of these config parameters and only if there is a need to change these defaults. @rabbah okay to delay loading these config parameters or do you need config loading already now?

@markusthoemmes please let me know whether anything is still required from your side.

@style95 please check whether you are ok.

I would like to get this PR merged if everybody is ok...

Nothing obvious here. Per error message it means that in PUT object flow one of the request is being missed by Minio. A typical put is a 3 step process involving preparing put, upload chunks and then stitch. 

From error message it means that one of the first 2 request was missed. May be enable proxy mode and see what request are being sent

```
whisk {
  s3 {
    alpakka {
      forward-proxy {
        host = "proxy-host"
        port = 8080
        credentials {
          username = "username"
          password = "password"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

And use something like [Charles Proxy](https://www.charlesproxy.com/) to see the requests made. May be that may provide some clue
